data.text: Goshi, I hope you and your family are all safe. I've been part of a huge, life changing disaster. Hurricane Katrina struck my hometown in 2005. All of my family members lost almost everything. Homes were destroyed, memories were lost, thankfully everyone was safe. Since then all the houses have been rebuilt and everyone is doing well. It wasn't an easy road but we are here. I know what your people will be going through. Have faith, be strong, and know that it will all be okay some day in the not too distant future.
